Mostly typical two-note calls (song?). Interesting interaction/fight with a second individual at 3:26.

There were 2 or 3 CAKI going off right outside the house so I grabbed my camera and went out to record thinking I could get some good vocalizations. The crux of this recording is approximately from 1:27 to 4:32 or so when a 2nd bird came in and the two started giving these soft growly / warbly / squeaky calls. I was maybe 30' away and the birds 1'-2' away from each other. They always seemed to be in these low bowing postures, bobbing a bit, and then turning backwards and forwards more-or-less 90 degrees to the branch they were on. They jumped from different branches a few times, but just kept it up until one of the birds, I presume the second, flew off. I stopped recording soon thereafter.
I think there were two birds hidden high in the tree
